EU changes rules for obtaining visa
People should go to service centers for Visa Applicants before his interview at the Consular Section, the cost will be lower and as the waiting time.
As of January 10, 2011 changed the procedure for processing a visa at the U.S. Embassy and consulates.
With the new procedure, most applicants must go to service centers for Visa Applicants (ASC, for its acronym in English) before his interview at the Consular Section.
ASC staff will take the applicant's biometric information, which will be reviewed by the consular section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for the applicants, among which are:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, and no payment will be required to make the appointment, another payment to process the visa application and another for the courier to deliver the document.
The applicant will only make a single payment covering the three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $ 140 for a tourist visa, $ 150 for visa cases to appeal (including visas for temporary workers) and $ 390 for visas for traders and investors.
Persons wishing to renew their visa will not have to attend an interview with a consular officer, but only attend the nearest ASC where they present their documents and take their fingerprints.
Because the biometric information will be made at the ASC, applicants who require a second appointment to be interviewed at the Consular Section, will remain in this less time than in the past.
Also, those applying for visa at the Consulate in Ciudad Juarez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo and not pay extra service fee of $ 26.
For additional information on the new visa application procedure, visit the following page http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
